        <section class="about">
            <h2>About the Legend</h2>
            <p>Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel (1875 - 1950) was a leader of the Indian National Congress and a key figure in India's independence movement and post-independence integration : <br><br> 
Independence movement : <br>
Patel was a leader in the fight for India's independence, organizing nonviolent civil disobedience against the British Raj. He was jailed multiple times for his patriotic efforts. <br><br>
Integration of India : <br>
After independence, Patel played a key role in integrating India, persuading rulers of princely states to join the union. He also helped frame the Constitution of India and establish administrative frameworks.<br><br> 
Home Minister and Deputy Prime Minister : <br>
Patel served as India's first Home Minister and first Deputy Prime Minister after independence. He also took charge of the Information and Broadcasting Ministry.<br><br> 
Partition of India : <br>
Patel was one of the first Congress leaders to accept that partition was a necessary solution to the separatist movement. He represented India in the Partition council, where he helped divide public assets.<br> <br>
Nickname : <br>Patel earned the nickname "Iron Man of India" for his ability to unite the nation through diplomacy and firmness. <br><br>
Death : <br>
Patel's health declined in 1950 and he died of a heart attack on December 15, 1950. <br><br></p>
